Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; set aside to soften (you'll use it in Step 4). Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @corn{1%unit}.

Melt @butter{}(2 tablespoons) in a medium #pot over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @flour{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1%minute}.

Slowly stir @milk{6.75%ounce} into pot a splash at a time until fully incorporated.

Stir in @water{1.5%cups}.

Add potatoes, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and half the @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1%unit} (you'll use more in the next step). Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. 

> To test, pierce one piece with a fork—it should go through easily.

Meanwhile, combine softened butter, @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1/4%tsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp} until smooth. (If the butter is still cold, microwave for ~{10%seconds} to soften.) Taste and add more Old Bay Seasoning if desired.

Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise; spread cut sides with Old Bay butter. Place cut sides up on a #baking sheet{}.

Toast on top rack until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once potatoes are tender, reduce heat to low and mash with a #potato masher{} or fork to desired consistency.

> We recommend mashing until almost smooth, leaving a few small potato pieces for texture.

Stir in @PHILADELPHIA® Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, corn, and @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} until fully incorporated and chowder is thick and creamy (it will be very thick at this point). If needed, stir in splashes of @water{} until chowder reaches desired consistency. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Halve Old Bay toast on a diagonal if desired.

Divide chowder between #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Serve with Old Bay toast on the side.